---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import CassettePlayer from '../components/CassettePlayer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title={`About — ${SITE_TITLE}`}
			description="About Rishabh Gupta — Computer Scientist at Adobe Acrobat Android, leading mobile growth and monetization engineering at billion-install scale."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<section class="reveal">
				<p class="eyebrow">About</p>
				<h1>I build mobile payments &amp; growth systems at billion-install scale.</h1>
			</section>

			<section class="reveal">
				<p>
					I&rsquo;m a Computer Scientist at Adobe Acrobat, where I lead
					growth, engagement, and monetization engineering for Acrobat
					Android. The app has 1B+ installs and 95M+ monthly active users
					globally, with payments served through Google Play Billing.
				</p>

				<p>My work spans three areas:</p>

				<ul>
					<li>
						<strong>Mobile payments platform.</strong>
						I own end-to-end stability of the in-app payments stack &mdash;
						integration with Play Billing, subscription state machines,
						receipt verification, observability, and the controlled-rollback
						playbook that keeps payments healthy across releases. Most
						recently I led the design and launch of Acrobat Mobile&rsquo;s
						first cross-product subscription upgrade / downgrade /
						cross-grade architecture, shipped in January 2026 with zero
						production incidents since launch and subsequently adopted by
						other Acrobat apps in the organization.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Growth engineering.</strong>
						I lead the engagement charter that grew annual subscription
						retention 35%, and shipped the server-driven, context-aware
						paywall surface that delivered a 15% FY24 upsell uplift. I
						also productionized our on-device ML personalization model
						for the upsell experience &mdash; handling TFLite integration,
						latency budgeting, and graceful fallbacks.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Mobile DevEx.</strong>
						I build the automations that let our Android organization ship
						monetization changes weekly: a Figma design linter (RTL, error
						states, click journeys, light/dark mode, font scaling,
						analytics coverage), an automated release-cherry-pick + Jira
						workflow, and a weekly executive KPI digest pipeline that
						ships a Monday-morning Slack message plus an auto-generated
						PowerPoint readout.
					</li>
				</ul>

				<p>
					Mentoring engineers earlier in their careers is also a
					meaningful share of what I do &mdash; I think it&rsquo;s one
					of the highest-leverage things a senior IC can spend time on.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="reveal">
				<h2>Earlier work</h2>
				<p>
					Before my current role, I was a Member of Technical Staff II at
					Adobe Acrobat (Dec 2021&ndash;Apr 2025), where I led the
					monetization and engagement charter on the same product.
				</p>
				<p>
					Before Adobe, I led mobile development at Aon (2018&ndash;2021)
					&mdash; built the original CoCubes Android app (50K+ downloads,
					4.1&#9733;), led the React Native v2 unifying iOS and Android,
					and revamped the Assessment app (150K+ downloads, 4.0&#9733;)
					for remote candidate proctoring under poor-network conditions.
				</p>
				<p>
					I started at Samsung R&amp;D as an intern on Samsung Pay,
					contributing to UPI / NPCI compliance hardening and production
					bug fixes.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="reveal">
				<h2>Background</h2>
				<p>
					B.E. Computer Science from R.V. College of Engineering, Bangalore
					(2014&ndash;2018, GPA 8.97/10). Based in Gurgaon, India.
				</p>
			</section>

